Name: REFERENCE POINT NAME
Explanation: SEE ATP 1, VOL 1, CHAPTER 2.

Name: CONTACT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE PERSON TO BE CONTACTED.

Name: AGENT NAME
Explanation: GIVES THE NAME OF INDIVIDUAL NBC AGENTS.

Name: NAME, INDIVIDUAL
Explanation: IDENTIFICATION OF A SPECIFIC HUMAN BEING THROUGH A COMBINATION OF WORDS.

Name: OVERLAY NAME
Explanation: A NAME USED TO IDENTIFY AN OVERLAY ASSOCIATED WITH A RECOGNIZED AIR, LAND OR MARITIME PICTURE.

Name: NAME OF UPPER AIR SOUNDING SYSTEM
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE ENVIRONMENTAL MONITORING SYSTEM USED FOR TAKING UPPER AIR SOUNDING.

Name: AIRSPACE COORDINATION AREA CODE NAME
Explanation: PROVIDES THE CODE NAME OF A PARTICULAR AIRSPACE COORDINATION AREA.

Name: SHIP NAME OR AGENCY ASSUMING CONTROL
ORDNANCE WEAPON AMMUNITION TYPE NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF AN ORDNANCE, WEAPON OR AMMUNITION.

Name: AREA OF VALIDITY
Explanation: THE NAME ASSIGNED TO THE AREA, WHERE A CERTAIN ORDER IS VALID OR ENFORCED.

Name: SURNAME OF A PERSON
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION OF A PERSON BY SURNAME.

Name: NAME OF ATMOSPHERIC RANGE PREDICTION MODEL
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE MODEL USED FOR DETERMINING ATMOSPHERIC ELECTROMAGNETIC PROPAGATION RANGES.

Name: AAR TRACK AREA
Explanation: THE AIR-TO-AIR REFUELING TRACK OR AREA NAME AS PROVIDED BY AJP 3.3.4.2 PARA 203.

Name: BULLSEYE POINT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A SPECIFIC SPACE POINT CALLED BULLSEYE.

Name: NAME OF SHIP CLASS
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE SHIP DESIGNATED AS THE PROTOTYPE OF A GROUP OF SHIPS OF THE SAME CLASS.

Name: DEFENDED ASSET NAME
Explanation: THE NAME BY WHOM A DEFENDED ASSET IS COMMONLY KNOWN.

Name: NAVIGATION AID NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A NAVIGATION AID.

Name: SHIP NICKNAME
Explanation: THE COLLOQUIAL NAME GIVEN TO A SHIP.

Name: COMMANDER NAVAL TASK DESIGNATOR NAME
Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION NAME OF THE COMMANDER OF A NAVAL TASK DESIGNATOR. FOR EXAMPLE "COMAIREASTLANT" OR "COMSTANAVFORLANT"

Name: FLAG SHIP
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE UNIT IN WHICH THE TASK ORGANISATION COMMANDER IS EMBARKED.

Name: RADIO SYSTEM, CIRCUIT, OR FACILITY NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A RADIO SYSTEM, CIRCUIT OR FACILITY.

Name: NAME OF LEAD SHIP IN GROUP
AREA WEAPON CONTROL AIRCRAFT
Explanation: THE NAME OF AN AREA WEAPON CONTROL AIRCRAFT.

Name: NAME OF ATMOSPHERIC RANGE PREDICTION COMPUTER
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE COMPUTER SYSTEM ON WHICH THE ATMOSPHERIC RANGE PREDICTION COMPUTER IS RUN.

Name: NATO SUB AREA NAME
Explanation: THE NAME DESIGNATING A NATO SUB AREA.

Name: NAME OF THERMOGRAPH SYSTEM
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE BATHYHERMOGRAPH SYSTEM.

Name: NAME OF SONAR RANGE PREDICTION MODEL
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE MODEL USED FOR DETERMINING SONAR PROPAGATION RANGES.

Name: LAUNCHING UNIT
Explanation: THE NAME, DESIGNATOR OR IDENTIFIER OF A UNIT LAUNCHING AIRCRAFT OR LANDING CRAFT.

Name: SITE NAME
Explanation: FOR THE NAME OF "SAM" OR "ELECTRONIC" SITES REFER TO USEUCOM EOB AND USAFE MOB INO REPORT 200-3.

Name: NAME OF SONAR RANGE PREDICTION COMPUTER
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE COMPUTER SYSTEM ON WHICH THE SONAR RANGE PREDICTION MODEL IS RUN.

Name: NOMENCLATURE
Explanation: THE NAME OF AN ITEM OR ARTICLE.

Name: NAME RANK OF CONTACT
Explanation: THE NAME AND RANK OF A PERSON TO BE CONTACTED.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER SYMBOLOGY, RESOLVED TO
Explanation: A DESCRIPTION OF THE RADAR WARNING RECEIVER MIPPLE SYMBOL INDICATIONS RESOLVED TO.

Name: SPECIAL CONFIGURATION EQUIPMENT NAME
Explanation: ANY EQUIPMENT INSTALLED ON AN AIRCRAFT WHICH IS NOT NORMALLY ASSOCIATED WITH THAT PARTICULAR AIRCRAFT.

Name: MISSION PLACE NAME
Explanation: A NAME THAT IDENTIFIES THE LOCATION AT WHICH A MISSION IS TO BE PERFORMED. THIS CAN BE THE NAME OF A GENERAL TARGET AREA, ORBIT, CAP POINT, STATION, ETC., FOR EXAMPLE: "MISTY ORBIT".

Name: DISPOSITION NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A FORCE DISPOSITION.

Name: DEPARTURE LOCATION NAME
Explanation: THE NAME BY WHOM THE LOCATION OF DEPARTURE OF AN AIRCRAFT IS COMMONLY KNOWN.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER SYMBOLOGY, TEMPORARY
Explanation: A DESCRIPTION OF THE RADAR WARNING RECEIVER TEMPORARY INDICATIONS.

Name: POL TYPE NAME
Explanation: DATA ITEMS ARE CONTAINED IN ACEREP VOL 6, LOGSTARS PART 2, LAND FORCES REPORTABLE ITEM LIST [LFRIL]. USE THE SHORT TITLES AS THE DATA CODES.

Name: REFERENCE NAME
Explanation: A NAME MUTUALLY AGREED UPON BY TWO OR MORE AGENCIES TO IDENTIFY AN OBJECT, UNIT OR GEOGRAPHIC LOCATION. THE NAME CAN BE A CALL SIGN, TACAN NAME, GEOGRAPHIC NAME, POINT NAME IN AN OPERATIONS ORDER, ETC.

Name: GEOGRAPHIC PLACE NAME
Explanation: THE GEOGRAPHIC PLACE NAME OF THE LOCATION OF THE EVENT BEING REPORTED.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER SYMBOL POSITION ON SCOPE
Explanation: THE POSITION OF RWR INDICATIONS AS DISPLAYED ON THE SCOPE AT TIME OF ENCOUNTER.

Name: FORCE OR UNIT REQUIRED TO ACKNOWLEDGE
AIR REFUELING CONTROL POINT
Explanation: THE NAME BY WHOM THE LOCATION OF THE AIR REFUELING CONTROL POINT IS COMMONLY KNOWN.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER OPERATIONAL FLIGHT PROGRAM
Explanation: THE RADAR WARNING RECEIVER OPERATIONAL FLIGHT PROGRAM FOR MISSION AIRCRAFT.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER MULTI FUNCTION DISPLAY
Explanation: THE RADAR WARNING RECEIVER MULTI-FUNCTION DISPLAY FOR MISSION AIRCRAFT.

Name: GATEWAY INSTALLATION NAME
Explanation: IAW STANAG 4211, THE FACILITY OR SITE NAME OF THE GATEWAY SWITCH.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER SYMBOLOGY, STEADY
Explanation: A DESCRIPTION OF THE RADAR WARNING RECEIVER STEADY SYMBOL INDICATIONS.

Name: RADAR WARNING RECEIVER SYMBOLOGY, MIPPLE
Explanation: A DESCRIPTION OF THE RADAR WARNING RECEIVER MIPPLE SYMBOL INDICATIONS.

Name: GATEWAY SWITCH IDENTIFIER
Explanation: THE IDENTIFICATION OF A GATEWAY NODE.

Name: UNIT PROVIDING HELICOPTERS
Explanation: THE NAME OF A UNIT PROVIDING HELICOPTERS FOR THE VERTICAL REPLENISHMENT OPERATION.

Name: UNIT BEING JOINED OR DETACHED FROM
CIRCUIT NAME IN ORDER OF PRIORITIES
CIRCUIT TITLE
Explanation: THE NAME IDENTIFYING A CIRCUIT ON A NETWORK.

Name: NAME OF COMMANDING OFFICER OF SHIP
RELATED ENTITY NAME
Explanation: GENERIC DESCRIPTOR FOR ANY SPECIFIC ENTITY NAME.

Name: UNIT PROVIDING CARGO OR PERSONNEL
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE UNIT PROVIDING CARGO OR PERSONNEL FOR VERTICAL REPLENISHMENT OPERATION.

Name: NAME OF FACTION
Explanation: A NAME OF A GROUP OR CLIQUE WITHIN A LARGER GROUP, PARTY, GOVERNMENT, OR ORGANIZATION.

Name: NEXT PORT OF CALL
Explanation: IF THE NAME EXCEEDS 20 CHARACTERS, IT CAN BE TRUNCATED.

Name: SUBSEQUENT PORT OF CALL
Explanation: IF THE NAME EXCEEDS 20 CHARACTERS, IT CAN BE TRUNCATED.

Name: PORT OF DISCHARGE
Explanation: THE PORT AT WHICH THE REPORTED CARGO WILL BE DISCHARGED. IF THE NAME EXCEEDS 20 CHARACTERS, IT CAN BE TRUNCATED.

Name: ON-CARRYING SHIP NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE SHIP CARRYING THE CARGO TO THE NEXT PORT.

Name: PORT OF LOADING
Explanation: THE PORT AT WHICH CARGO IS LOADED ON A DEPARTING SHIP. IF THE NAME EXCEEDS 20 CHARACTERS, IT CAN BE TRUNCATED.

Name: RETURN PORT
Explanation: THE PORT TO WHICH A SHIP RETURNS AFTER DISCHARGING ITS CARGO. IF THE NAME EXCEEDS 20 CHARACTERS, IT CAN BE TRUNCATED.

Name: CONSIGNEE
Explanation: THE DESIGNATION OF THE AGENT, ACTIVITY, OR ORGANIZATION TO WHICH CARGO IS CONSIGNED.

Name: HELICOPTER CONTROL UNIT
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE UNIT CONTROLLING THE SPECIFIED HELICOPTER(S).

Name: EMERGENCY LANDING PROVISION
Explanation: THE NAME OF A UNIT OR AREA DESIGNATED AS THE EMERGENCY LANDING LOCATION FOR THE SPECIFIED HELICOPTER(S).

Name: NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP NAME
Explanation: THE LINK 16 NETWORK PARTICIPATION GROUP (NPG) NAME.

Name: UNIT PROVIDING FUEL
Explanation: THE NAME OF A UNIT, OTHER THAN THE PARENT UNIT, REQUIRED TO PROVIDE FUELLING FACILITIES FOR THE SPECIFIED HELICOPTER(S).

Name: NAME OR IDENTIFICATION OF CONTROLLING AGENCY
LIFEGUARD UNIT
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE UNIT DESIGNATED AS LIFEGUARD FOR THE REPLENISHMENT AT SEA OPERATION.

Name: MINE MARK MOD
Explanation: SEE ATP-6, VOLUME 1, ANNEX 4A.

Name: SEARCH ATTACK UNIT OR SURFACE ACTION GROUP COMMANDER
NADGE SITE DESIGNATOR
Explanation: NATO AIR DEFENCE GROUND ENVIRONMENT DESIGNATOR.

Name: SURVEILLANCE AREA NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A SURVEILLANCE AREA WHERE AN AIRBORNE EARLY WARNING OPERATION IS TAKING PLACE.

Name: GROUNDSITE NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A GROUNDSITE UNIT.

Name: CLASS NAME OF THE PRIMARY SHIP TARGET
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE SHIP DESIGNATED AS THE PROTOTYPE OF A GROUP OF SHIPS OF THE SAME CLASS.

Name: CLASS NAME OF THE SECONDARY SHIP TARGET
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE SHIP DESIGNATED AS THE PROTOTYPE OF A GROUP OF SHIPS OF THE SAME CLASS.

Name: NAME OF ZONE OF FIRE
Explanation: THE SECTOR OF RESPONSIBILITY FOR A FIRE SUPPORT UNIT.

Name: FIELD LOCATION NAME OF ENEMY
Explanation: NAME OF AN ENEMY LOCATION.

Name: CODED LOCATION NAME
Explanation: A REFERENCE TO A LOCATION OTHER THAN BY LATITUDE OR LONGITUDE, THAT IS AGREED AND CONTAINED IN OTHER DOCUMENTS (OPERATIONS ORDERS, FIRE SUPPORT PLANS ETC.).

Name: EMITTER NAME
Explanation: THE ASSIGNED NAME OF A PARTICULAR EMITTER, OPERATION OR STATION.

Name: SHIP CLASS NAME
Explanation: VESSEL CLASS NAME GIVEN TO ONE OR MORE VESSELS BECAUSE OF A SIMILARITY IN CONFIGURATION, CAPABILITY, AND CONSTRUCTION HISTORY.

Name: AIRSPACE COORDINATION AREA NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF AN AIRSPACE COORDINATION AREA.

Name: INGRESS ROUTE IDENTIFICATION
Explanation: THE NAME ASSIGNED TO SPECIFICALLY IDENTIFY AN INBOUND ROUTE TO A SPECIFIC AREA OR TARGET.

Name: EGRESS ROUTE IDENTIFICATION
Explanation: THE NAME ASSIGNED TO SPECIFICALLY IDENTIFY AN OUTBOUND ROUTE FROM A SPECIFIC AREA OR TARGET.

Name: EXIT POINT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME ASSIGNED TO A POINT ESTABLISHED AS THE EXIT POSITION FOR A ROUTE.

Name: TARGET FACILITY NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A TARGET/FACILITY, ABBREVIATED.

Name: ENTRY POINT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME ASSIGNED TO A POINT ESTABLISHED AS THE ENTRY POSITION FOR A ROUTE.

Name: ADDRESS PLACE NAME
Explanation: A CITY, TOWN, VILLAGE WHERE A UNIT, FACILITY, OR INSTALLATION IS LOCATED. [REF.: STANAG 2438, 2439, 2440, AINTP-3]

Name: ALTERNATE NAME
Explanation: ALTERNATE NAME BY WHICH AN EVENT, PLACE, INSTALLATION, FACILITY OR UNIT IS KNOWN. [REF.: STANAG 2438, 2439, 2441, AINTP-3]

Name: STREET NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF A STREET ON WHICH A FACILITY OR INSTALLATION IS LOCATED USED IN THE ADDRESS. [REF: AINTP-3]

Name: ALSO PRODUCED AS
Explanation: NAME OF THE OTHER ORGANIZATION AND THE NAME UNDER WHICH IT PRODUCES THE EQUIPMENT IF THIS IS DIFFERENT FROM THAT OF THE BASIC EQUIPMENT. [REF: STANAG 2097, AINTP-3]

Name: DERIVED FROM
Explanation: NAME OF THE SOURCE EQUIPMENT. [REF: STANAG 2097, AINTP-3]

Name: BATTLEFIELD GEOMETRY TYPE NAME
Explanation: THE NAME ASSIGNED TO A BATTLEFIELD GEOMETRY TYPE FOR PURPOSES OF IDENTIFICATION.

Name: ESTABLISHING AUTHORITY
Explanation: THE DESIGNATOR OR IDENTIFIER OF THE UNIT WHICH HAS THE AUTHORITY TO ESTABLISH OR COORDINATE THE BATTLEFIELD GEOMETRY.

Name: EVENT NAME
Explanation: AGREED NAME OF AN EVENT. [STANAG 2441, AINTP-3]

Name: LAST NAME
Explanation: DEFINES THE SURNAME, OR GIVEN NAME CONFERRED UPON AN INDIVIDUAL AT BIRTH, THROUGH MARRIAGE, OR THROUGH A LEGAL PROCESS. IT CAN ALSO BE THE FAMILY NAME.

Name: FIRST NAME(S)
Explanation: INDICATES THE CHOSEN NAME(S) CONFERRED UPON AN INDIVIDUAL OTHER THAN HIS LAST NAME, BY WHICH HE IS FAMILIARLY KNOWN.

Name: MIDDLE NAME(S) INITIAL(S)
Explanation: INDICATES THE CHOSEN NAME(S) CONFERRED UPON AN INDIVIDUAL, APART FROM HIS FIRST AND LAST NAMES. THESE NAMES MAY BE EXPRESSED THROUGH THE USE OF THE INITIAL LETTERS.

Name: BIRTH NAME
Explanation: INDICATES THE FAMILY NAME CONFERRED UPON AN INDIVIDUAL AT BIRTH E.G. MAIDEN NAME.

Name: PLACE NAME, EXTENDED
Explanation: THE GENERALLY UNDERSTOOD NAME OF THE PLACE.

Name: DESTINATION PLACE NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE INTENDED PLACE OF ARRIVAL OF A PERSON OR OBJECT.

Name: INPORT PLACE NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE PORT AT WHICH A PERSON OR OBJECT IS CURRENTLY.

Name: BRAND NAME
Explanation: THE NAME DESIGNATED FOR A PRODUCT BY THE MANUFACTURER.

Name: NAME OF ORIGINAL CLASSIFICATION AUTHORITY
Explanation: MARKINGS THAT INDICATE THE ORIGINAL CLASSIFICATION AUTHORITY FOR A MESSAGE.

Name: LINK NAME
Explanation: FIELD FORMAT USED TO INDICATE IN FREE TEXT THE RECOGNIZED NETWORK OR LINK NAME.

Name: ZONE NAME
Explanation: IDENTIFICATION OF THE LANDING ZONE.

Name: NAME OF NEAREST TOWN
Explanation: GIVES THE NAME OF THE NEAREST TOWN TO IDENTIFY AND SPECIFY A GEOGRAPHIC POSITION.

Name: NAME AND ADDRESS OF MOVEMENT AGENCY
Explanation: GIVES THE NAME OF THE NATIONAL HQ ISSUING THE MOVEMENT CREDIT.

Name: TARGET LIST NAME
Explanation: A NAME USED TO IDENTIFY THE TARGET LIST.

Name: AIRCRAFT MANUFACTURER
Explanation: IDENTIFIES THE MANUFACTURER OF AN AIRCRAFT.

Name: FORCE NAME
Explanation: THE SPECIFIC NAME FOR A GIVEN FORCE.

Name: GRID NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OR DESIGNATOR OF A SPECIFIC GRID USED FOR FORCE DISPOSITION IN TACTICAL MARITIME OPERATIONS.

Name: NAME OF UNIT CARGO RECEIVED FROM
NAME OF ORIGINATING UNIT OF CASUALTY
NAME OF PRESENT LOCATION OF CASUALTY
NAME OF LOCATION FROM WHICH THE CASUALTY WAS RECEIVED
NAME OF LOCATION TO WHICH THE CASUALTY WAS MEDEVACED
NAME OF LOCATION TO WHICH THE CASUALTY IS PENDING MEDEVAC
SECURITY CLASSIFICATION AUTHORITY
Explanation: ACTUAL (ABBREVIATED) NAME OF THE AUTHORITY THAT ASSIGNED THE FIRST SECURITY CLASSIFICATION.

Name: COLLECTION PROGRAMME OR PLATFORM
Explanation: IDENTIFIES THE PLATFORM OR PROGRAMME THAT WAS USED TO COLLECT THE IMAGERY.

Name: IDENTIFICATION GATE NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OR DESIGNATION OF AN IDENTIFICATION GATE USED FOR AIRCRAFT CONTROL PURPOSES.

Name: SECTOR ANTI-AIR WARFARE COORDINATOR (SAAWC)
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE UNIT DESIGNATED AS SECTOR ANTI-AIR WARFARE COORDINATOR.

Name: COMMERCIAL OWNER
Explanation: THE COMMERCIAL NAME OF AN OWNER OF AN OBJECT.

Name: TASK NAME
Explanation: A WORD OR A COMBINATION OF WORDS BY WHICH A TASK IS KNOWN AND IDENTIFIED.

Name: SHIP DEPARTMENT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OR IDENTIFIER OF A PARTICULAR DEPARTMENT OR SUB-DIVISION OF A SHIP'S INTERNAL ORGANISATION.

Name: AOA APPROACH FORMATION
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE AMPHIBIOUS OBJECTIVE AREA (AOA) APPROACH FORMATION.

Name: SUPPORTED UNIT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE SUPPORTED UNIT.

Name: LAUNCH UNIT NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE LAUNCH UNIT.

Name: LOADING SHIP NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OF THE LOADING SHIP

Name: LCS NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OR DESIGNATOR OF THE LANDING CRAFT AIR CUSHION (LCAC) CONTROL SHIP (LCS).

Name: LCAC LANDING ZONE NAME
Explanation: THE DESIGNATOR OF THE LCAC LANDING ZONE ASSIGNED TO THE LCAC CONTROL SHIP (LCS), REPEATING AS NECESSARY FOR ALL ZONES ASSIGNED.

Name: HCS LANDING ZONE NAME
Explanation: THE DESIGNATOR OF THE HCS LANDING ZONE ASSIGNED TO THE HELICOPTER CONTROL SHIP (HCS), REPEATING AS NECESSARY FOR ALL ZONES ASSIGNED.

Name: HT AREA NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OR IDENTIFIER ASSIGNED TO THE HELICOPTER TRANSPORT AREA.

Name: SHIP ENTRY SEQUENCE
Explanation: THE NAME OF A SHIP IN THE TASK FORCE, REPEATING AS NECESSARY IN ORDER OF SHIP ENTRY.

Name: HCS NAME
Explanation: THE NAME OR DESIGNATOR OF THE HELICOPTER CONTROL SHIP (HCS).

Name: SCREEN NAME
Explanation: IDENTIFIES A SCREEN BY NAME

Name: COMMUNICATION CHANNEL
Explanation: THE COMMUNICATION CHANNEL NAME IN FREE TEXT.

Name: INTERROGATOR LAST NAME
Explanation: DEFINES THE SURNAME CONFERRED UPON THE INTERROGATOR AT BIRTH, THROUGH MARRIAGE OR THROUGH A LEGAL PROCESS.

Name: AIR COMMAND AND CONTROL SYSTEM (ACCS) DESIGNATION
COMMUNICATIONS PATH
Explanation: DEFINES THE COMMUNICATION PATH TO BE USED.
